│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs due to an assertion in SystemZTTIImpl::getCastInstrCost that forbids vector destination types (!Dst->isVectorTy()). SLP revectorization queries cast costs for  │
│ vector types during horizontal reductions, so this restriction is too strict and triggers the abort. To fix, we should relax the assertion and implement a reasonable cost model for      │
│ vector casts: if either Src or Dst is a vector, compute cost per element and multiply by the vector width, falling back to a simple heuristic cost. I will modify                         │
│ llvm/lib/Target/SystemZ/SystemZTargetTransformInfo.cpp to remove the assertion and add handling for vector types.                                                                         │
